content:
Control Visible Work Item Details in Omni-Channel with Compact Layouts

Ever wanted to customize the information that your agents see when they get a new work item in Omni-Channel? You can! Just customize primary compact layout for that work item’s object.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Omni-Channel:	Customize Application

If you look closely, you’ll notice that a few fields are visible by default on new work item requests. For example, if your agent receives a request to manage a case, the request features the case’s priority, status, and case number by default.

TIP There’s only so much room to display fields on work item requests. While you can technically put up to 10 fields on a compact layout, Omni-Channel displays only 4 fields. As a best practice, select up to 4 of the most important fields that you want to expose on work item requests.

Decide which object’s compact layout you want to edit.
From the management settings for the object whose work item you want to edit, select Compact Layouts, and then select New.
Select the settings for your compact layout, including the fields that you want it to include.
Click Save.
Change the primary compact layout to your new layout by clicking Compact Layout Assignment | Edit Assignment.
Select your new compact layout from the Primary Compact Layout drop-down list.
Click Save.
title: Customize Omni-Channel Work Item Details
